WEBVTT

00:02.102 --> 00:03.536
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

00:03.602 --> 00:05.071
<i>- ♪ Timmy's</i>
<i>still an average kid ♪</i>

00:05.138 --> 00:07.340
<i>♪ That no one understands ♪</i>

00:07.407 --> 00:09.442
<i>♪ Chloe's his new neighbor ♪</i>

00:09.509 --> 00:11.878
<i>♪ And she's ruining</i>
<i>all his plans ♪</i>

00:11.945 --> 00:12.912
- Ahh!

00:12.979 --> 00:13.913
<i>- ♪ All the wishes ♪</i>

00:13.980 --> 00:15.081
<i>♪ In the world ♪</i>

00:15.148 --> 00:17.250
<i>♪ So why should he care? ♪</i>

00:17.317 --> 00:19.552
<i>♪ Jorgen has reported</i>
<i>there's a fairy shortage ♪</i>

00:19.619 --> 00:21.755
<i>♪ So Timmy has to share ♪</i>

00:21.821 --> 00:24.758
<i>♪ His OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:24.824 --> 00:27.260
- More than one?
- This should be fun!

00:27.327 --> 00:29.229
<i>- ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:29.295 --> 00:32.232
<i>♪ Feather suit, nature boots,</i>
<i>laser shooting, rescue ♪</i>

00:32.298 --> 00:33.466
- World peace, kale treats,

00:33.533 --> 00:34.667
bunny feet, real neat!

00:34.734 --> 00:35.802
- What? No!
Leave me alone!

00:35.869 --> 00:38.438
My fairies!
Get your own!

00:38.505 --> 00:40.807
-<i> ♪ OddParents,</i>
<i>fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:40.874 --> 00:42.776
<i>♪ Timmy, beware,</i>
<i>you'll have to share ♪</i>

00:42.842 --> 00:43.977
{\an8}<i>♪ Your fairly OddParents ♪</i>

00:44.043 --> 00:45.078
{\an8}- Yeah, right!

00:50.083 --> 00:53.019
<i>[heroic theme]</i>

00:53.086 --> 00:58.491
<i>♪</i> ♪

00:58.558 --> 01:00.059
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

01:00.126 --> 01:02.562
- Well, the school week's over
and I'm just itching

01:02.629 --> 01:05.565
to do something selfless
and kind for a stranger!

01:05.632 --> 01:07.867
{\an1}- Maybe I'll share my nuts
with a stranger!

01:07.934 --> 01:09.035
{\an3}- Oh dear.

01:09.102 --> 01:10.303
- But not my almonds.

01:10.370 --> 01:12.806
{\an1}And I'm definitely keeping
my pistachios.

01:12.872 --> 01:14.941
{\an1}And everyone better just keep
their filthy hands

01:15.008 --> 01:16.876
off my fancy cashews!

01:16.943 --> 01:18.244
Don't even look at them!

01:18.311 --> 01:20.246
- And resetting.
Ooh!

01:20.313 --> 01:22.782
{\an1}Maybe we could save
a troubled animal species!

01:22.849 --> 01:25.885
- It's the weekend,
Sally Saverson! Relax!

01:25.952 --> 01:27.787
{\an3}- Aah!
Save the puppy!

01:27.854 --> 01:30.423
<i>[heavy metal music plays]</i>

01:30.490 --> 01:32.292
{\an3}- This isn't even
a real puppy.

01:32.358 --> 01:34.794
{\an3}It's Dark Laser's
stupid toy dog, Flipsie!

01:34.861 --> 01:37.697
{\an3}- Oh, I hope Dark Laser
isn't around.

01:37.764 --> 01:40.400
{\an3}He's dedicated his life
to destroying Timmy!

01:40.467 --> 01:42.168
{\an1}- Well,
a lot of people have.

01:42.235 --> 01:44.370
{\an1}Timmy's inspirational
that way.

01:44.437 --> 01:45.705
Stop staring at my nuts!

01:45.772 --> 01:48.708
[electronic whirring]

01:48.775 --> 01:51.711
<i>[ominous music]</i>

01:51.778 --> 01:54.747
<i>♪</i> ♪

01:54.814 --> 01:56.015
- I will destroy you...

01:56.082 --> 01:57.550
[all screaming]

01:57.617 --> 01:59.252
{\an3}- Is what I will say
when I find

01:59.319 --> 02:01.654
{\an3}the fiends who nearly ran over
my beloved Flipsie!

02:01.721 --> 02:03.122
Oh, Flipsie!

02:03.189 --> 02:04.224
Please be able to flip!

02:04.290 --> 02:05.525
I don't want to have call you

02:05.592 --> 02:07.894
Mister-Just-
Lays-There-With-Dead-Eyes!

02:07.961 --> 02:10.797
Also, that name would never fit
on your doggie dish.

02:10.864 --> 02:12.131
[sobs]

02:12.198 --> 02:13.132
{\an1}[barks]

02:13.199 --> 02:14.167
Oh, he flipped!

02:14.234 --> 02:15.168
It's a miracle!

02:15.235 --> 02:17.103
[giggles]

02:17.170 --> 02:18.104
Wow!

02:18.171 --> 02:19.439
I was just gonna chill

02:19.506 --> 02:20.673
with my best bros
Foop and Mr. Crocker,

02:20.740 --> 02:21.908
and possibly,
but not necessarily

02:21.975 --> 02:23.443
destroy you, Timmy,

02:23.510 --> 02:25.612
when Flipsie suddenly
flipped out of my spaceship!

02:25.678 --> 02:27.347
That's the last time
Daddy lets you ride

02:27.413 --> 02:29.983
with your handsome little face
out the window, Mister!

02:30.049 --> 02:31.751
[laughs]

02:31.818 --> 02:33.219
[snarling]

02:33.286 --> 02:35.388
<i>♪</i> ♪

02:35.455 --> 02:36.923
[roars]

02:36.990 --> 02:38.525
<i>♪</i> ♪

02:38.591 --> 02:42.328
- Um, Mr. Laser sir, may I ask
what was that horrifying beast

02:42.395 --> 02:43.696
with eight rows of teeth?

02:43.763 --> 02:46.466
{\an3}- Oh, that was a Depravulak,
little blonde one.

02:46.533 --> 02:48.001
{\an3}The most vicious
predator in the galaxy.

02:48.067 --> 02:51.471
I was transporting it
to a scary zoo on Carniveron 5.

02:51.538 --> 02:52.906
You don't have
a pig, do you?

02:52.972 --> 02:54.707
- Uh, no.
- Good!

02:54.774 --> 02:56.075
{\an3}'Cause that thing can eat
a Christmas ham

02:56.142 --> 02:57.477
{\an3}in the blink
of an eye.

02:57.544 --> 03:00.046
{\an1}- You're not going
to destroy Timmy, are you?

03:00.113 --> 03:02.015
{\an3}- No,
strange talking squirrel.

03:02.081 --> 03:03.416
Timmy and the blonde one saved

03:03.483 --> 03:06.452
{\an3}the thing that is
most dear to me, Flipsie!

03:06.519 --> 03:08.354
According to
the Cyborg Code of Honor,

03:08.421 --> 03:10.256
I must now devote my life
to protecting them

03:10.323 --> 03:12.525
from all threats
to their happiness.

03:12.592 --> 03:14.060
- As long as you keep
your grubby paws

03:14.127 --> 03:18.498
off my fancy cashews,
I don't care what you do.

03:18.565 --> 03:21.501
- Wait! Whoa! Wait!
So you're like our bodyguard?

03:21.568 --> 03:23.036
Count me in,
Dark Laser!

03:23.102 --> 03:25.471
- Why don't you call me
by my given name, Clark?

03:25.538 --> 03:28.975
{\an3}I changed it to "Dark"
during my emo teen years.

03:29.042 --> 03:30.043
I was quite the handful.

03:30.109 --> 03:32.779
[chuckles]

03:32.845 --> 03:35.448
- Timmy, do you seriously want
to spend the rest of your life

03:35.515 --> 03:37.517
{\an1}guarded by a highly unstable
man-machine

03:37.584 --> 03:39.586
with plasma cannons for arms?

03:39.652 --> 03:41.854
{\an3}- Uh, yeah!
Who wouldn't? Trust me!

03:41.921 --> 03:43.289
This is gonna be awesome.

03:43.356 --> 03:44.290
- Oh, Timmy!

03:44.357 --> 03:45.825
If you want your allowance,

03:45.892 --> 03:48.061
stop lollygagging with
your terrifying metal friend

03:48.127 --> 03:49.696
and mow the lawn!

03:49.762 --> 03:53.933
- Uh, Clark? The lawn thing is a
definite threat to my happiness.

03:54.000 --> 03:55.301
- Terminating threat.

03:55.368 --> 03:56.302
- [screams]

03:56.369 --> 03:57.870
Here's your allowance!

03:57.937 --> 03:59.939
{\an1}And take these bars of gold
I keep in my pockets,

04:00.006 --> 04:01.240
both in case of an emergency

04:01.307 --> 04:04.143
{\an1}and because they make
my thighs look muscular!

04:04.210 --> 04:05.411
{\an3}- Whoo hoo!

04:05.478 --> 04:07.714
{\an1}- I feel a sense
of impending doom.

04:07.780 --> 04:09.782
{\an3}- Does it feel like
the hot, sticky breath

04:09.849 --> 04:11.351
of a space monster?

04:11.417 --> 04:12.885
{\an3}'Cause I'm
feeling that.

04:12.952 --> 04:15.788
{\an3}[growls]

04:15.855 --> 04:18.791
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

04:18.858 --> 04:22.028
<i>♪</i> ♪

04:22.095 --> 04:25.498
[screaming]

04:25.565 --> 04:27.734
- You seem tense,
little blonde one.

04:27.800 --> 04:29.369
{\an3}- Do I?

04:29.435 --> 04:30.536
{\an3}Perhaps it's because people
are scattering in sheer terror

04:30.603 --> 04:32.138
at the very sight of us.

04:32.205 --> 04:33.406
{\an1}- You know,
I like the scattering.

04:33.473 --> 04:35.274
Makes me feel macho.

04:35.341 --> 04:36.542
{\an1}But if it bothers you,
all we have to do

04:36.609 --> 04:38.811
is give Dark Laser
a little makeover.

04:38.878 --> 04:40.013
{\an1}Cosmo?

04:42.849 --> 04:45.084
- Oh wow, I am too good!

04:45.151 --> 04:47.820
Now I can't tell
Timmy and Dark Laser apart.

04:47.887 --> 04:49.288
- Honestly.

04:49.355 --> 04:51.591
I don't think anyone else is
going to have that problem.

04:51.658 --> 04:53.793
{\an1}- Timmy, I'm sorry for being
a Wendy Whateverwart,

04:53.860 --> 04:57.030
{\an1}but there's no upside
to having a homicidal cyborg

04:57.096 --> 04:59.699
as my bodyguar--littering alert!

04:59.766 --> 05:03.936
Hooligans are befouling the
fragile ecosystem of our park!

05:04.003 --> 05:06.272
- Terminating threat.

05:06.339 --> 05:08.474
[all shriek]

05:10.610 --> 05:12.712
- Take that,
enemies of nature!

05:12.779 --> 05:13.946
Booyah!

05:14.013 --> 05:15.848
I have to admit,
I enjoyed that immensely.

05:15.915 --> 05:18.951
- Cosmo, do you smell
Christmas ham?

05:19.018 --> 05:20.887
- Oh, whenever possible.

05:20.953 --> 05:23.389
Why?

05:23.456 --> 05:26.893
[cell phone rings]

05:26.959 --> 05:28.928
- Excuse me.

05:28.995 --> 05:30.163
[both giggling]

05:30.229 --> 05:31.564
- Throw the toilet paper!

05:31.631 --> 05:33.466
Hey, bestie!
Where you at?

05:33.533 --> 05:35.535
You wanna help me and Foop
TP Turner's house?

05:35.601 --> 05:37.737
And maybe demolish it
afterwards?

05:37.804 --> 05:39.605
[laughing]

05:39.672 --> 05:41.407
{\an3}- Love to.
But alas, I cannot.

05:41.474 --> 05:42.809
Also, if you guys TP the house,

05:42.875 --> 05:45.011
{\an3}I will be forced
to annihilate you both.

05:45.078 --> 05:46.813
- Whoa!
Mood swings much?

05:46.879 --> 05:48.481
Did we say something
to offend you?

05:48.548 --> 05:50.349
{\an3}I hope not.
He has a Death Laser.

05:50.416 --> 05:52.218
- It's not you.
It's me.

05:52.285 --> 05:53.653
I am duty-bound to protect Timmy

05:53.720 --> 05:55.555
because he
saved Flipsie's life,

05:55.621 --> 05:58.858
and since you guys are
a threat to Timmy, we--

05:58.925 --> 06:00.827
Just say it, Laser.

06:00.893 --> 06:03.863
We can no longer be bros.
[sobbing]

06:03.930 --> 06:05.732
{\an1}- Yeah, I'm gonna skip
right over the fact

06:05.798 --> 06:09.035
{\an1}that Flipsie was never alive
to begin with and say...

06:09.102 --> 06:10.770
that really stings, man!

06:10.837 --> 06:12.772
{\an3}- Don't make it harder
than it already is, Denzel.

06:12.839 --> 06:14.741
{\an3}You and Foop
just have to move on.

06:14.807 --> 06:17.009
- If--if that's
what you want.

06:17.076 --> 06:18.611
- You know it isn't!

06:18.678 --> 06:20.046
- Wait!

06:20.113 --> 06:21.881
- I love you!

06:21.948 --> 06:23.382
- Are you okay, Clark?

06:23.449 --> 06:25.218
{\an3}You look even more unstable
than normal.

06:25.284 --> 06:26.686
Which is alarming.

06:26.753 --> 06:28.588
- All that matters is that,
thanks to you and Timmy,

06:28.654 --> 06:30.490
I still have my Flipsie!

06:30.556 --> 06:32.058
Who's Daddy's little
life partner?

06:32.125 --> 06:33.726
[coos]

06:33.793 --> 06:36.429
{\an1}- All right, let's not spoil
a great day with icky emotions.

06:36.496 --> 06:37.630
Let's just celebrate

06:37.697 --> 06:39.232
{\an1}that thanks
to the Cyborg Code of Honor

06:39.298 --> 06:41.801
things are awesome for me
and they're only going

06:41.868 --> 06:42.869
to get better!

06:42.935 --> 06:44.337
[both scream]

06:44.403 --> 06:46.072
{\an3}[snarling]

06:52.078 --> 06:53.579
- [yelps]

06:53.646 --> 06:54.614
Hey!
Honey!

06:54.680 --> 06:56.616
Call our insurance guy.

06:56.682 --> 07:00.019
I think I just hit
an invisible bear!

07:00.086 --> 07:02.488
{\an3}- It's been a fun day,
but I'm having second thoughts

07:02.555 --> 07:04.023
about this whole thing.

07:04.090 --> 07:05.358
{\an1}- Well that's because you're
a Cindy Secondthoughts,

07:05.424 --> 07:06.692
Wendy Worrywart!

07:06.759 --> 07:08.795
{\an1}- You have nothing to fear,
little blonde one.

07:08.861 --> 07:10.730
To assure your safety
during feeding time,

07:10.797 --> 07:12.098
or as you call it, night,

07:12.165 --> 07:15.535
{\an1}I will encase you
in a nuclear force-field.

07:15.601 --> 07:16.903
{\an3}- Oh yeah!
Check it!

07:16.969 --> 07:18.838
{\an3}You're in a
crackling nuclear bubble.

07:18.905 --> 07:20.540
{\an3}What kid
wouldn't want that?

07:20.606 --> 07:21.974
Say it with me:

07:22.041 --> 07:25.144
Everything is awesome!

07:25.211 --> 07:27.613
[grunts]

07:29.248 --> 07:31.984
- Uh, it's just not
the same without him.

07:32.051 --> 07:33.719
- Cosmo! Wanda!
Where were you guys?

07:33.786 --> 07:36.255
- We were chased away
by a terrible thing

07:36.322 --> 07:37.757
with ham breath!

07:37.824 --> 07:39.225
- Ah!
It could be anywhere.

07:39.292 --> 07:40.560
Or everywhere.

07:40.626 --> 07:42.995
- No need to fear,
strange talking fish.

07:43.062 --> 07:44.730
The Depravulak
is nowhere nearby.

07:44.797 --> 07:46.632
But if it does eventually
catch you,

07:46.699 --> 07:48.601
take solace in the fact
that the end will be quick.

07:48.668 --> 07:50.970
{\an1}- Well, that's a relief.
Wait, what?

07:51.037 --> 07:53.739
- Sleep tight and don't let
the Depravulaks bite.

07:53.806 --> 07:55.374
Remember, they have
eight rows of teeth.

07:55.441 --> 07:56.976
[chuckles]

07:57.043 --> 07:58.110
- Uh, wait a minute.

07:58.177 --> 07:59.445
I thought you said
the Depravulak

07:59.512 --> 08:01.214
was nowhere nearb--Clark?

08:01.280 --> 08:02.481
- [snores]

08:02.548 --> 08:03.683
[chuckles]
Flipsie.

08:03.749 --> 08:06.385
[cell phone rings]

08:06.452 --> 08:08.354
- What is it now,
Kelly Callerson?

08:08.421 --> 08:09.355
- I can't sleep, Timmy.

08:09.422 --> 08:10.957
My bubble is buzzing

08:11.023 --> 08:15.394
{\an3}and I can't reach my juice
box through the force-field.

08:15.461 --> 08:16.662
Help.

08:16.729 --> 08:18.431
- Everything is awesome!

08:18.497 --> 08:19.999
[snores]

08:20.066 --> 08:21.400
[rooster crows]

08:21.467 --> 08:22.969
- [screams]

08:23.035 --> 08:24.670
{\an3}- [screams]

08:24.737 --> 08:26.072
- The world is ending!

08:26.138 --> 08:28.741
{\an1}I'm late for school!
For the first time ever!

08:28.808 --> 08:32.010
{\an1}I overslept!
The bubble fried my alarm clock!

08:32.078 --> 08:32.945
- No worries!

08:33.011 --> 08:34.080
I can get you to school on time.

08:34.145 --> 08:35.681
Even if you're
already late.

08:35.748 --> 08:36.883
Isn't that right, Flipsie?

08:36.948 --> 08:38.583
[babbles]

08:38.650 --> 08:40.119
<i>♪</i> ♪

08:40.186 --> 08:41.320
<i>Hang on, kids.</i>

08:41.386 --> 08:42.755
In order to get
to school on time,

08:42.822 --> 08:44.657
we'll be traveling
through a wormhole.

08:44.724 --> 08:46.125
{\an3}- Is that like a manhole
for worms?

08:46.192 --> 08:47.326
No, that's stupid.

08:47.393 --> 08:48.427
{\an1}- A wormhole is a distortion
in space

08:48.494 --> 08:49.662
that can reverse time

08:49.729 --> 08:50.897
{\an1}and get us to
school before the bell,

08:50.963 --> 08:52.899
{\an1}or tear us
into a gazillion pieces.

08:52.965 --> 08:55.401
{\an1}A risk I
am willing to take.

08:55.468 --> 08:58.404
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

08:58.471 --> 09:05.144
<i>♪</i> ♪

09:05.211 --> 09:06.379
[both screaming]

09:06.445 --> 09:08.848
<i>♪</i> ♪

09:12.018 --> 09:13.085
- Where are we?

09:13.152 --> 09:15.554
{\an1}I just saw a mosquito
the size of a bus!

09:15.621 --> 09:17.089
- We're at school.

09:17.156 --> 09:18.724
Or the place where school
will eventually be built.

09:18.791 --> 09:20.559
We went just a touch
too far back in time,

09:20.626 --> 09:23.629
so class won't be starting
for another 3.5 million years.

09:23.696 --> 09:24.997
- What?
- Whoa!

09:25.064 --> 09:26.699
both: No!

09:26.766 --> 09:28.034
- We can pass the time

09:28.100 --> 09:29.535
by telling
knock-knock jokes with Flipsie.

09:29.602 --> 09:30.870
Knock knock.

09:30.937 --> 09:32.538
{\an3}Flipsie takes a little time
to answer.

09:32.605 --> 09:35.074
{\an3}But relax,
we have 3.5 million years.

09:35.141 --> 09:36.442
{\an3}[giggles]

09:36.509 --> 09:38.511
{\an8}<i>[bright music]</i>

09:38.577 --> 09:39.512
- Ah!

09:39.578 --> 09:41.247
So glad to be home!

09:41.314 --> 09:42.782
Wilma!
Chasmo!

09:42.848 --> 09:44.917
I missed you so much!
I really did!

09:44.984 --> 09:47.119
Flipsie! Knock knock!
What's the answer?

09:47.186 --> 09:49.121
{\an1}- Who's there?
Answer me, Flipsie!

09:49.188 --> 09:50.256
[frantic gibberish]

09:50.323 --> 09:51.557
- The big mosquito ate
a caveman!

09:51.624 --> 09:53.159
Flipsie!
There was a lot of blood.

09:53.225 --> 09:54.894
It was really gross.

09:54.961 --> 09:57.930
- You two need a sec?
[both screaming]

09:57.997 --> 09:59.498
- Yes. Chloe, I was so wrong

09:59.565 --> 10:01.167
about the whole
bodyguard thing!

10:01.233 --> 10:03.736
{\an3}I was Ricky Wrongface
and you were Rita Righterson!

10:03.803 --> 10:05.204
both: Whisper whisper.

10:05.271 --> 10:07.673
{\an1}- Clark, what would it take
to end our arrangement?

10:07.740 --> 10:09.875
{\an1}If we did, in fact
wish to end it, that is.

10:09.942 --> 10:10.977
{\an3}- Which we do!
Flipsie!

10:11.043 --> 10:12.878
{\an3}Knock knock!
Please end now!

10:12.945 --> 10:14.680
- All you have to do is ask.

10:14.747 --> 10:16.115
both: Whoo hoo!

10:16.182 --> 10:17.216
- Consider it over!

10:17.283 --> 10:19.719
Soon! Pronto! Now!
Get out of here!

10:19.785 --> 10:21.821
- Flipsie!
We're free!

10:21.887 --> 10:23.622
You two kids have
my eternal thanks!

10:23.689 --> 10:25.491
Now I must go
while I can still resist

10:25.558 --> 10:28.694
the urge to destroy you,
Timmy Turner.

10:28.761 --> 10:30.629
<i>♪</i> ♪

10:30.696 --> 10:32.031
- You did the right thing,
Sport.

10:32.098 --> 10:34.467
- But only after doing
the wrong thing.

10:34.533 --> 10:35.735
That's our Timmy.

10:35.801 --> 10:37.236
[car tires squeal]

10:37.303 --> 10:38.371
- Hey!

10:38.437 --> 10:41.440
- BFFs, I missed you so bad!

10:41.507 --> 10:42.541
- Hop in, bestie!

10:42.608 --> 10:43.743
We have enough
toilet paper

10:43.809 --> 10:44.910
to TP the
principal's house!

10:44.977 --> 10:47.246
Grab a roll
and let's roll!

10:47.313 --> 10:49.115
- Wait a minute.
What's that music?

10:49.181 --> 10:51.851
- It's my favorite band,
Prison Bus!

10:51.917 --> 10:53.352
{\an3}- We like to listen to it
real loud

10:53.419 --> 10:55.755
{\an3}and drive recklessly through
the streets of Dimmsdale!

10:55.821 --> 10:57.790
{\an3}[cackles]
And hit small dogs!

10:59.825 --> 11:02.962
<i>[heavy metal music plays]</i>

11:03.029 --> 11:05.664
<i>♪</i> ♪

11:05.731 --> 11:06.999
- Uh-huh...

11:07.066 --> 11:09.402
{\an3}Hey BFFs, heh,
maybe I'll just meet you

11:09.468 --> 11:10.636
at the principal's place.

11:10.703 --> 11:12.204
In the meantime,
allow me to gift you

11:12.271 --> 11:15.741
this Christmas ham
I happen to be carrying. Hmm?

11:15.808 --> 11:18.811
- Yay!
I love un-refrigerated meat!

11:24.383 --> 11:27.319
[all laughing]

11:31.290 --> 11:32.491
<i>♪</i> ♪

11:32.558 --> 11:34.160
{\an1}- I feel a sense
of impending doom.

11:34.226 --> 11:37.029
{\an3}- I just feel hot, sticky breath
on the back of my neck.

11:37.096 --> 11:38.964
{\an3}And I gotta say,
I like it.

11:39.031 --> 11:40.433
[snarls]

11:40.499 --> 11:42.601
[both scream]

11:42.668 --> 11:45.671
<i>♪</i> ♪

11:50.309 --> 11:53.245
<i>[upbeat music]</i>

11:53.312 --> 11:59.018
<i>♪</i> ♪

11:59.085 --> 12:01.921
[school bell rings]

12:01.987 --> 12:03.155
- Red alert!

12:03.222 --> 12:04.490
According to my
Crocker Cranky Meter,

12:04.557 --> 12:07.526
Mr. Crocker's at
Level Grumpy Old Man!

12:07.593 --> 12:09.028
{\an1}Oh no!

12:09.095 --> 12:11.130
When Crocker's in a bad mood
he blames everything on me.

12:11.197 --> 12:12.731
- Timmy, you take Mr. Crocker's

12:12.798 --> 12:16.168
{\an3}delightfully dystopian
world view way too personally.

12:16.235 --> 12:19.772
{\an3}He doesn't
really blame you.

12:19.839 --> 12:21.407
- It's time to play
Wheel of Blame!

12:21.474 --> 12:23.042
Where I spin the wheel

12:23.109 --> 12:25.644
and blame the pathetic farce
that is my life on Timmy Turner!

12:25.711 --> 12:28.047
[all cheering]

12:28.114 --> 12:29.615
My flat feet!

12:29.682 --> 12:31.283
My podiatrist says it's genetic,
but I blame Turner!

12:31.350 --> 12:32.618
Detention!

12:32.685 --> 12:34.120
- Timmy, I might have been
a smidge wrong

12:34.186 --> 12:35.521
about the blame thing.

12:35.588 --> 12:37.089
- Mother, I'm a grown man.

12:37.156 --> 12:40.159
{\an1}I don't need my Mommy barging in
on my place of business.

12:40.226 --> 12:41.227
- I brought your lunch.

12:41.293 --> 12:42.228
- Yippee!

12:42.294 --> 12:43.229
Thank you, Mommy!

12:43.295 --> 12:44.663
Kisses!

12:44.730 --> 12:46.732
Gah! You didn't cut
my pimento loaf sandwich

12:46.799 --> 12:48.434
into the shape
of a feral wolverine

12:48.501 --> 12:49.435
the way I like it!

12:49.502 --> 12:51.170
- I blame Timmy Turner.

12:51.237 --> 12:53.005
- Oh, come on!

12:53.072 --> 12:54.440
- Detention to infinity!

12:54.507 --> 12:56.542
Thanks to you, I'm in no mood
to teach today.

12:56.609 --> 12:59.211
So I'm gonna to put on
this video of paint drying.

12:59.278 --> 13:01.914
[all groaning]

13:01.981 --> 13:04.650
<i>♪</i> ♪

13:04.717 --> 13:06.685
You don't like it?
Blame Turner!

13:06.752 --> 13:08.254
Works for me.

13:08.320 --> 13:09.321
- Ooh!

13:09.388 --> 13:10.489
I love this movie.

13:10.556 --> 13:12.625
{\an1}The characters have
so many layers!

13:12.691 --> 13:14.793
- Layers of paint!
Drying!

13:14.860 --> 13:17.830
- Timmy, my internship
at the cuckoo hospital

13:17.897 --> 13:19.598
{\an3}leads me to believe
that Mr. Crocker

13:19.665 --> 13:22.067
might be blaming you
because he's unhappy.

13:22.134 --> 13:24.436
- No kidding, Dr. Duh!

13:24.503 --> 13:25.604
- He needs a heart-to-heart talk

13:25.671 --> 13:27.439
with one Chloe Carmichael.

13:27.506 --> 13:29.642
I'm like a gondolier
guiding people

13:29.708 --> 13:32.478
through the troubled waters
of their lives.

13:32.545 --> 13:34.013
{\an3}Mr. Crocker,
I know I'm just a student

13:34.079 --> 13:36.048
and you might not feel
entirely comfortable

13:36.115 --> 13:37.249
sharing your feelings but--

13:37.316 --> 13:38.817
- I'm so lonely!

13:38.884 --> 13:41.287
{\an1}I'm a middle-aged man
with a hump, weird hair,

13:41.353 --> 13:43.689
and an obsession
with fairies and cat figurines

13:43.756 --> 13:44.924
who lives
with his mother.

13:44.990 --> 13:45.925
Newsflash!

13:45.991 --> 13:47.760
I'm not a chick magnet!

13:47.826 --> 13:49.895
I'm too miserable
to even blame Turner.

13:49.962 --> 13:52.765
Which I blame on Turner!

13:52.831 --> 13:53.999
- Good talk.

13:54.066 --> 13:56.168
I don't want to be a gondolier
anymore.

13:56.235 --> 13:59.605
<i>So I think if Mr. Crocker</i>
<i>gets a girlfriend</i>

13:59.672 --> 14:01.907
{\an3}he'd be happier and stop
blaming you for everything.

14:01.974 --> 14:04.210
-The only way we can
get Mr. Crocker a girlfriend

14:04.276 --> 14:07.780
is with a Taser and a net
and I think that's illegal.

14:07.846 --> 14:11.016
{\an3}- Or, we could
wish one up for him.

14:11.083 --> 14:16.422
{\an3}Cosmo, Wanda, it's time
for Operation Build-A-Babe.

14:18.324 --> 14:21.260
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:21.327 --> 14:22.928
<i>♪</i> ♪

14:22.995 --> 14:26.465
{\an3}- Okay, we have to make her
attracted to Mr. Crocker.

14:26.532 --> 14:29.535
{\an1}But one small problem:
she has eyes!

14:29.602 --> 14:31.470
{\an3}- What if we just give her
really bad eyesight?

14:31.537 --> 14:36.141
{\an1}- It's gotta be
really bad.

14:36.208 --> 14:37.910
- Oops!

14:37.977 --> 14:39.845
I hit the wrong button and
"Paint Dry Two" is in Spanish.

14:39.912 --> 14:41.747
Now I don't know
what's happening!

14:41.814 --> 14:43.582
- If we're going to create
Mr. Crocker's dream girl,

14:43.649 --> 14:45.351
they have to have
things in common.

14:45.417 --> 14:47.553
{\an3}Hmm, what does he enjoy
besides misery?

14:47.620 --> 14:49.922
{\an1}- Uh, well, cat figurines,
baton twirling,

14:49.989 --> 14:55.060
{\an1}and telling really,
really bad jokes.

14:56.996 --> 14:59.565
- And if our cupid's arrow
is going to hit a bull's-eye,

14:59.632 --> 15:02.501
we can't forget
the most important thing of all!

15:02.568 --> 15:04.003
Mr. Crocker's girlfriend

15:04.069 --> 15:07.873
should really, really, really,
reeaallly like him!

15:07.940 --> 15:11.076
{\an3}- Oh boy, that's going to take
a lot of power.

15:11.143 --> 15:14.013
{\an3}We're going to need
our back-up batteries.

15:20.085 --> 15:22.588
- Oh, and she catches flies
with her tongue.

15:22.655 --> 15:25.124
A little somethin' for me.

15:25.190 --> 15:28.027
- Wait, what?

15:28.093 --> 15:29.762
- Hiiiiiiiiiiii!!!

15:29.828 --> 15:32.264
[laughs]

15:32.331 --> 15:34.867
- [yelps]

15:36.402 --> 15:38.904
- It's alive!

15:38.971 --> 15:41.874
- Why did the chicken
cross the road?

15:41.940 --> 15:44.376
It could be
for a variety of reasons.

15:44.443 --> 15:46.578
[laughs]

15:46.645 --> 15:48.547
- Wow, that's not even a joke.

15:48.614 --> 15:51.350
{\an1}We've created the most
annoying woman on Earth.

15:51.417 --> 15:53.919
She's perfect!

15:53.986 --> 15:55.587
{\an3}- You're going to like
Mr. Crocker.

15:55.654 --> 15:56.989
He's a bundle of fun!

15:57.056 --> 16:00.426
<i>- [Mr. Crocker weeps]</i>

16:00.492 --> 16:01.927
<i>So lonely!</i>

16:01.994 --> 16:06.065
- Get ready to meet the man
of your dreams.

16:06.131 --> 16:07.099
<i>- Human contact!</i>

16:07.166 --> 16:08.100
<i>I'll get it!</i>

16:08.167 --> 16:09.101
<i>Stop laughing, Mother!</i>

16:09.168 --> 16:10.436
<i>It could be for me.</i>

16:10.502 --> 16:15.174
Turner, I blame--
you gotta be kidding me!

16:15.240 --> 16:16.675
Hello!

16:16.742 --> 16:18.677
- Mr. Crocker, I'd like you
to meet my Aunt--

16:18.744 --> 16:20.179
we forgot to give her a name.

16:20.245 --> 16:21.814
- Hummanuh, hummanuh!

16:21.880 --> 16:23.215
- Yes!
How did you know?

16:23.282 --> 16:24.383
{\an3}Her name
is Hummanuh Hummanuh.

16:24.450 --> 16:26.618
But you can call
her...Hummanuh?

16:26.685 --> 16:30.389
{\an3}Aunt Hummanuh,
say hi to Mr. Crocker.

16:30.456 --> 16:33.058
- No, that's a ficus.

16:33.125 --> 16:35.294
And that's a jar that says,
"Broken Dreams."

16:35.361 --> 16:36.495
- Never mind that!

16:36.562 --> 16:39.465
- This is Mr. Crocker.

16:39.531 --> 16:41.066
- Hiiiiiiiii!

16:41.133 --> 16:43.168
{\an1}[laughs]

16:43.235 --> 16:45.037
- I must be in heaven
because I just heard

16:45.104 --> 16:46.805
the voice of an angel.

16:46.872 --> 16:48.907
- Wow, I heard the voice
of a dying raccoon,

16:48.974 --> 16:50.909
but hey,
if it works for you.

16:50.976 --> 16:53.779
- Care to join me
in a love montage?

16:53.846 --> 16:55.314
I blame you, Turner...

16:55.381 --> 16:57.916
for finding
the love of my life!

16:57.983 --> 17:00.452
both: Yeah!

17:00.519 --> 17:01.920
-<i> ♪ Love, love, love ♪</i>

17:01.987 --> 17:04.189
<i>♪ Crocker's in</i>
<i>love, love, love ♪</i>

17:04.256 --> 17:05.656
<i>♪ Like a flock</i>
<i>of brain-dead doves ♪</i>

17:05.723 --> 17:08.627
<i>♪ Crocker's in love ♪</i>

17:08.694 --> 17:10.128
<i>♪ Love, love, love ♪</i>

17:10.194 --> 17:15.200
<i>♪ Crocker's in</i>
<i>love, love, love ♪</i>

17:15.267 --> 17:17.869
<i>♪ Whooooo ♪</i>

17:17.935 --> 17:20.372
<i>♪ They're in love ♪</i>

17:20.439 --> 17:22.141
<i>♪ Love, love ♪</i>

17:22.207 --> 17:23.909
<i>♪ Love, love ♪</i>

17:23.976 --> 17:26.011
<i>♪ Love, love, love, love ♪</i>

17:26.078 --> 17:28.480
<i>♪ Mr. Crocker's in love ♪</i>

17:28.547 --> 17:29.715
<i>♪ Love, love, love ♪</i>

17:29.782 --> 17:34.253
<i>♪ Yeah, they're in love ♪</i>

17:34.319 --> 17:35.554
- It's a school night, Sport.

17:35.621 --> 17:37.456
Shouldn't you be doing homework?

17:37.523 --> 17:38.924
- Don't have to.

17:38.991 --> 17:40.826
Ever since I set Mr. Crocker
up with Hummanuh,

17:40.893 --> 17:43.395
he's so happy he stopped
blaming me for everything.

17:43.462 --> 17:46.131
{\an1}And he automatically
gives me As!

17:46.198 --> 17:47.533
- Oh, Timmy!

17:47.599 --> 17:49.134
Who's the lady living here

17:49.201 --> 17:51.103
with a voice like someone
put a trumpet in a blender?

17:51.170 --> 17:52.204
- Aunt Hummanuh.

17:52.271 --> 17:53.639
Uh, your sister.

17:53.705 --> 17:54.807
- I don't have a sister.

17:54.873 --> 17:56.241
- Yes, you do.
- Okay!

17:56.308 --> 17:58.410
Hey, sis!

17:58.477 --> 17:59.411
Noogies!

17:59.478 --> 18:00.712
- Stop it!

18:00.779 --> 18:02.648
I'm tellin'.

18:02.714 --> 18:04.583
- Ow! Mom!

18:04.650 --> 18:06.618
Hummanuh pinched me!

18:06.685 --> 18:09.021
- Do I have to separate you two
again?

18:09.087 --> 18:11.924
- Dearest Hummanuh, I brought
you a bouquet of batons.

18:11.990 --> 18:13.292
I sprung for the full dozen.

18:13.358 --> 18:14.293
And I never spring.

18:14.359 --> 18:15.894
I'm not a springer!

18:15.961 --> 18:18.931
- Okay, now why don't you two
spring on out of here?

18:18.997 --> 18:22.167
- Oh!
They're beautiful.

18:22.234 --> 18:23.268
Knock knock.

18:23.335 --> 18:24.436
- Oh, I know how to play!

18:24.503 --> 18:25.771
Who's there?

18:25.838 --> 18:27.206
- I don't know.

18:27.272 --> 18:28.207
You knocked.

18:28.273 --> 18:29.374
Wait, I did.

18:29.441 --> 18:30.509
Never mind.

18:30.576 --> 18:32.544
{\an1}[laughs]

18:32.611 --> 18:33.745
{\an3}- [laughs]

18:33.812 --> 18:35.314
Killer looks and
killer punchlines!

18:35.380 --> 18:38.951
I'm the luckiest man alive!

18:39.017 --> 18:40.752
- Uh, a little room, people.

18:40.819 --> 18:43.755
{\an3}- ♪ Hummanuh and Crocker
sitting in a tree ♪

18:43.822 --> 18:47.025
♪ K-I-S-S-I-P-P-I ♪

18:47.092 --> 18:48.393
{\an1}Aaah!

18:48.460 --> 18:49.728
I'm telling!

18:49.795 --> 18:51.563
- You're my schmoopy,
boopy, floopy,

18:51.630 --> 18:54.032
doopy, moopy, poopy, zoopy.

18:54.099 --> 18:57.369
- No, you're my schmoopy,
boopy, floopy,

18:57.436 --> 18:59.638
doopy, moopy, poopy, zoopy.

18:59.705 --> 19:02.174
- No, you're my --

19:02.241 --> 19:03.709
- Make it stop!

19:03.775 --> 19:05.844
- Get used to it, Turner,
because I'm never leaving

19:05.911 --> 19:07.546
{\an3}my schmoopy, boopy,
floopy, doopy,

19:07.613 --> 19:10.315
moopy, poopy,
zoopy's side.

19:10.382 --> 19:13.318
- My life's worse than when
Mr. Crocker was blaming me.

19:13.385 --> 19:16.288
- Oh Timmy, you just don't
appreciate romance.

19:16.355 --> 19:18.190
Love is a beautiful thing.

19:18.257 --> 19:21.226
<i>[Crocker and Hummanuh</i>
<i>laugh maniacally]</i>

19:21.293 --> 19:22.261
Okay, that's nuts.

19:22.327 --> 19:23.428
Make it stop!

19:23.495 --> 19:25.330
{\an1}- Cosmo, Wanda,
I wish Aunt Hummanuh

19:25.397 --> 19:27.199
would go away-a-nuh!

19:27.266 --> 19:29.535
- Sorry Sport,
but as weird as it is,

19:29.601 --> 19:31.403
Mr. Crocker and Hummanuh
are in love

19:31.470 --> 19:34.039
and we're not allowed
to unwish true love.

19:34.106 --> 19:36.408
<i>[Mr. Crocker and Hummanuh</i>
<i>scream]</i>

19:36.475 --> 19:37.809
{\an1}- Uh oh.

19:37.876 --> 19:38.977
{\an1}Something happened to
schmoopy, boopy, floopy --

19:39.044 --> 19:42.548
{\an3}- I get it!
Let's go!

19:42.614 --> 19:43.682
{\an3}- Turner!
Chloe!

19:43.749 --> 19:45.417
I'm as giddy as a teenage girl!

19:45.484 --> 19:48.153
Hummanuh just proposed!

19:48.220 --> 19:49.655
- Nice rock!

19:49.721 --> 19:51.290
{\an3}- Oh, we're going to spend
the rest of our lives

19:51.356 --> 19:52.591
in Mother's basement!

19:52.658 --> 19:55.994
- I'm so happy for me, uh, you!

19:56.061 --> 19:59.298
{\an1}- Oh, I'm too classy
to live in a basement.

19:59.364 --> 20:02.334
I want our own place.

20:02.401 --> 20:03.502
- Good idea.

20:03.569 --> 20:04.736
I'll tell Mother
to pack up

20:04.803 --> 20:05.837
her collection
of celebrity hair.

20:05.904 --> 20:07.806
We're all moving to new digs!

20:07.873 --> 20:10.776
- I'm not living
with your mother.

20:10.842 --> 20:12.511
{\an3}- What?
No Mommy?

20:12.578 --> 20:13.645
- That's right.

20:13.712 --> 20:15.247
You have to choose.

20:15.314 --> 20:19.151
Me or your Mommy.

20:19.217 --> 20:21.753
{\an3}- Sweet, dear Hummanuh, I can't
lose the love of my life.

20:21.820 --> 20:24.756
{\an3}The choice is
obvious.

20:24.823 --> 20:26.425
I pick Mommy!

20:26.491 --> 20:28.660
- That's a good one.

20:28.727 --> 20:30.062
- I'm not joking, Hummanuh.

20:30.128 --> 20:31.997
{\an1}You're great, but Mother and I
share a history.

20:32.064 --> 20:33.832
Sure, it's checkered
and chronically unhealthy,

20:33.899 --> 20:35.300
but it's ours!

20:35.367 --> 20:40.472
{\an1}It's been fun Hummanuh,
but I'm done-a-nuh!

20:40.539 --> 20:41.940
- I feel strange.

20:42.007 --> 20:44.176
I've never been dumped before.

20:44.242 --> 20:46.511
{\an1}- Because she's
only two days old.

20:46.578 --> 20:49.114
- Hummanuh mad!

20:49.181 --> 20:52.117
Hummanuh smash!

20:52.184 --> 20:54.152
<i>♪</i> ♪

20:54.219 --> 20:57.155
[snarling]

20:57.222 --> 20:58.156
<i>♪</i> ♪

20:58.223 --> 21:01.426
[all screaming]

21:01.493 --> 21:02.494
<i>- Mom!</i>

21:02.561 --> 21:05.998
<i>Hummanuh broke the house!</i>

21:06.064 --> 21:07.566
- She's turned
into a girl-zilla!

21:07.633 --> 21:10.702
- Because she's been rejected
by her true love.

21:10.769 --> 21:12.738
It's so romantic!

21:12.804 --> 21:14.573
- I inspire rage in women!

21:14.640 --> 21:16.108
That's neat!

21:16.174 --> 21:17.175
[screams]

21:17.242 --> 21:18.410
Mommy!

21:18.477 --> 21:26.418
<i>♪</i> ♪

21:32.724 --> 21:34.092
- Our plan better work

21:34.159 --> 21:35.827
or it's back
to the wheel of blame for me!

21:35.894 --> 21:37.329
Oh, and Dimmsdale
will be destroyed.

21:37.396 --> 21:40.098
- The best way for Hummanuh
to get over Mr. Crocker

21:40.165 --> 21:42.200
is for us to wish up
someone new.

21:42.267 --> 21:43.502
- Ooh!

21:43.568 --> 21:46.638
Especially if he's
a hunkadoodledoo!

21:46.705 --> 21:48.707
<i>♪</i> ♪

21:48.774 --> 21:49.708
- Aunt Hummanuh!

21:49.775 --> 21:51.443
This is our friend...

21:51.510 --> 21:54.112
We forgot to give him a name.

21:54.179 --> 21:57.082
- Yowza!

21:57.149 --> 21:59.685
- That's right!
His name is Yowza.

21:59.751 --> 22:01.453
<i>♪</i> ♪

22:01.520 --> 22:04.456
- [laughs]

22:04.523 --> 22:07.759
- [grunts]

22:07.826 --> 22:10.195
- [giggles]

22:10.262 --> 22:11.229
<i>♪</i> ♪

22:11.296 --> 22:13.198
- [screams]

22:13.265 --> 22:16.101
- Mommy's got you, Denzel.

22:16.168 --> 22:18.570
<i>♪</i> ♪

22:18.637 --> 22:20.906
- Your training as a stunt pilot
finally paid off.

22:20.972 --> 22:21.907
- I know, I know.

22:21.973 --> 22:22.908
You blame me.

22:22.974 --> 22:24.242
- Yes, I do.

22:24.309 --> 22:25.711
For helping me see
that I already have

22:25.777 --> 22:27.012
the woman of my dreams,

22:27.079 --> 22:30.582
and her name is Mother!

22:30.649 --> 22:31.616
A feral wolverine!

22:31.683 --> 22:33.485
You remembered!

22:33.552 --> 22:34.619
And a real wolverine.

22:34.686 --> 22:36.321
Gah! Ah.

22:36.388 --> 22:37.389
